{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":567,"text":"In the 17th century, a woman named Giulia Tofana"},{"time":5098,"text":"had a very successful perfume business."},{"time":7809,"text":"For over 50 years she ran it."},{"time":10066,"text":"It sort of ended abruptly when she was executed — (Laughter) —"},{"time":12851,"text":"for murdering 600 men. You see, it wasn't a very good perfume."},{"time":18282,"text":"In fact, it was completely odorless and tasteless and colorless,"},{"time":22148,"text":"but as a poison, it was the best money could buy,"},{"time":25472,"text":"so women flocked to her in order to murder their husbands."}]},{"cues":[{"time":29265,"text":"It turns out that poisoners were a valued and feared group,"},{"time":34525,"text":"because poisoning a human being is a quite difficult thing."},{"time":38694,"text":"The reason is, we have sort of a built-in poison detector."},{"time":42029,"text":"You can see this as early as even in newborn infants."},{"time":45293,"text":"If you are willing to do this, you can take a couple of drops"},{"time":47864,"text":"of a bitter substance or a sour substance,"},{"time":50427,"text":"and you'll see that face, the tongue stick out, the wrinkled nose,"},{"time":54199,"text":"as if they're trying to get rid of what's in their mouth."},{"time":57071,"text":"This reaction expands into adulthood and becomes"},{"time":60023,"text":"sort of a full-blown disgust response, no longer just"},{"time":63543,"text":"about whether or not we're about to be poisoned,"},{"time":65995,"text":"but whenever there's a threat of physical contamination"},{"time":68952,"text":"from some source. But the face remains strikingly similar."},{"time":73083,"text":"It has expanded more, though, than just keeping us away"},{"time":77036,"text":"from physical contaminants, and there's a growing"},{"time":79217,"text":"body of evidence to suggest that, in fact, this emotion"},{"time":82700,"text":"of disgust now influences our moral beliefs"},{"time":85742,"text":"and even our deeply held political intuitions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":89638,"text":"Why this might be the case?"},{"time":93274,"text":"We can understand this process by understanding"},{"time":96269,"text":"a little bit about emotions in general. So the basic human emotions,"},{"time":99419,"text":"those kinds of emotions that we share with all other human beings,"},{"time":102614,"text":"exist because they motivate us to do good things"},{"time":105415,"text":"and they keep us away from doing bad things."},{"time":107726,"text":"So by and large, they are good for our survival."},{"time":111109,"text":"Take the emotion of fear, for instance. It keeps us away"},{"time":113918,"text":"from doing things that are really, really risky."},{"time":116422,"text":"This photo taken just before his death — (Laughter) —"},{"time":120262,"text":"is actually a — No, one reason this photo is interesting"},{"time":123108,"text":"is because most people would not do this, and if they did,"},{"time":126725,"text":"they would not live to tell it, because fear would have"},{"time":128725,"text":"kicked in a long time ago to a natural predator."},{"time":132400,"text":"Just like fear offers us protective benefits, disgust seems"},{"time":136007,"text":"to do the same thing, except for what disgust does is"},{"time":138341,"text":"keeps us away from not things that might eat us,"},{"time":140936,"text":"or heights, but rather things that might poison us,"},{"time":143601,"text":"or give us disease and make us sick."},{"time":146198,"text":"So one of the features of disgust that makes it such"},{"time":149455,"text":"an interesting emotion is that it's very, very easy to elicit,"},{"time":154238,"text":"in fact more so than probably any of the other basic emotions,"},{"time":157121,"text":"and so I'm going to show you that with a couple of images"},{"time":159490,"text":"I can probably make you feel disgust."},{"time":161373,"text":"So turn away. I'll tell you when you can turn back."},{"time":164568,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":165701,"text":"I mean, you see it every day, right? I mean, come on. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":170034,"text":"(Audience: Ewww.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":171247,"text":"Okay, turn back, if you didn't look."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174256,"text":"Those probably made a lot of you in the audience"},{"time":176791,"text":"feel very, very disgusted, but if you didn't look,"},{"time":180626,"text":"I can tell you about some of the other things that have been shown"},{"time":183156,"text":"sort of across the world to make people disgusted,"},{"time":185839,"text":"things like feces, urine, blood, rotten flesh."},{"time":189443,"text":"These are the sorts of things that it makes sense"},{"time":191277,"text":"for us to stay away from, because they might actually contaminate us."},{"time":194531,"text":"In fact, just having a diseased appearance"},{"time":196826,"text":"or odd sexual acts, these things are also"},{"time":199226,"text":"things that give us a lot of disgust."}]},{"cues":[{"time":202217,"text":"Darwin was probably one of the first scientists"},{"time":204595,"text":"to systematically investigate the human emotions,"},{"time":206538,"text":"and he pointed to the universal nature and the strength"},{"time":210227,"text":"of the disgust response."},{"time":212076,"text":"This is an anecdote from his travels in South America."}]},{"cues":[{"time":215347,"text":"\"In Tierro del Fuego a native touched with his finger"},{"time":217083,"text":"some cold preserved meat while I was eating ..."},{"time":219588,"text":"and plainly showed disgust at its softness, whilst I felt"},{"time":223107,"text":"utter disgust at my food being touched by a naked savage — (Laughter) —"},{"time":226105,"text":"though his hands did not appear dirty.\""},{"time":228262,"text":"He later wrote, \"It's okay, some of my best friends are naked savages.\" (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":233660,"text":"Well it turns out it's not only old-timey British scientists"},{"time":236404,"text":"who are this squeamish. I recently got a chance"},{"time":238685,"text":"to talk to Richard Dawkins for a documentary,"},{"time":240975,"text":"and I was able to disgust him a bunch of times. Here's my favorite."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244842,"text":"Richard Dawkins: \"We've evolved around courtship and sex,"},{"time":247207,"text":"are attached to deep-rooted emotions and reactions"},{"time":250229,"text":"that are hard to jettison overnight.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":254929,"text":"David Pizarro: So my favorite part of this clip is that"},{"time":258966,"text":"Professor Dawkins actually gagged."},{"time":261609,"text":"He jumps back, and he gags, and we had to do it three times,"},{"time":265194,"text":"and all three times he gagged. (Laughter)"},{"time":268750,"text":"And he was really gagging. I thought he might throw up on me, actually."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271896,"text":"One of the features, though, of disgust,"},{"time":275112,"text":"is not just its universality and its strength,"},{"time":278042,"text":"but the way that it works through association."},{"time":281081,"text":"So when one disgusting thing touches a clean thing,"},{"time":284816,"text":"that clean thing becomes disgusting, not the other way around."},{"time":288170,"text":"This makes it very useful as a strategy if you want to"},{"time":291377,"text":"convince somebody that an object or an individual"},{"time":293143,"text":"or an entire social group is disgusting and should be avoided."},{"time":296811,"text":"The philosopher Martha Nussbaum points this out"},{"time":299352,"text":"in this quote: \"Thus throughout history, certain disgust"},{"time":301436,"text":"properties -- sliminess, bad smell, stickiness, decay, foulness --"},{"time":304677,"text":"have been repeatedly and monotonously been associated with ..."},{"time":306977,"text":"Jews, women, homosexuals, untouchables, lower-class people --"},{"time":310829,"text":"all of those are imagined as tainted by the dirt of the body.\""},{"time":314343,"text":"Let me give you just some examples of how, some powerful"},{"time":317475,"text":"examples of how this has been used historically."},{"time":319847,"text":"This comes from a Nazi children's book published in 1938:"},{"time":323437,"text":"\"Just look at these guys! The louse-infested beards,"},{"time":326247,"text":"the filthy, protruding ears, those stained, fatty clothes..."},{"time":329557,"text":"Jews often have an unpleasant sweetish odor."},{"time":332323,"text":"If you have a good nose, you can smell the Jews.\""},{"time":335116,"text":"A more modern example comes from people who try to"},{"time":337649,"text":"convince us that homosexuality is immoral."},{"time":340110,"text":"This is from an anti-gay website, where they said"},{"time":343795,"text":"gays are \"worthy of death for their vile ... sex practices.\""},{"time":347072,"text":"They're like \"dogs eating their own vomit and sows wallowing in their own feces.\""},{"time":350738,"text":"These are disgust properties that are trying to be directly"},{"time":353482,"text":"linked to the social group that you should not like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356831,"text":"When we were first investigating the role of disgust in"},{"time":359603,"text":"moral judgment, one of the things we became interested in"},{"time":363472,"text":"was whether or not these sorts of appeals are more likely"},{"time":367775,"text":"to work in individuals who are more easily disgusted."},{"time":370840,"text":"So while disgust, along with the other basic emotions,"},{"time":372969,"text":"are universal phenomena, it just really is true"},{"time":375585,"text":"that some people are easier to disgust than others."},{"time":377883,"text":"You could probably see it in the audience members"},{"time":379569,"text":"when I showed you those disgusting images."},{"time":381626,"text":"The way that we measured this was by a scale that was"},{"time":384326,"text":"constructed by some other psychologists"},{"time":386655,"text":"that simply asked people across a wide variety of situations"},{"time":389512,"text":"how likely they are to feel disgust."},{"time":391613,"text":"So here are a couple of examples."},{"time":393406,"text":"\"Even if I were hungry, I would not drink a bowl of my"},{"time":395578,"text":"favorite soup if it had been stirred by a used but thoroughly washed fly-swatter.\""},{"time":399386,"text":"\"Do you agree or disagree?\" (Laughter)"},{"time":400951,"text":"\"While you are walking through a tunnel under a railroad track,"},{"time":403231,"text":"you smell urine. Would you be very disgusted or not at all disgusted?\""},{"time":406895,"text":"If you ask enough of these, you can get a general overall"},{"time":409551,"text":"score of disgust sensitivity."},{"time":411914,"text":"It turns out that this score is actually meaningful."},{"time":414387,"text":"When you bring people into the laboratory and you ask"},{"time":417464,"text":"them if they're willing to engage in safe but disgusting behaviors"},{"time":421293,"text":"like eating chocolate that's been baked to look like dog poop,"},{"time":426315,"text":"or in this case eating some mealworms that are perfectly healthy but pretty gross,"},{"time":430280,"text":"your score on that scale actually predicts whether or not"},{"time":433271,"text":"you'll be willing to engage in those behaviors."}]},{"cues":[{"time":435614,"text":"The first time that we set out to collect data on this"},{"time":438212,"text":"and associate it with political or moral beliefs,"},{"time":440222,"text":"we found a general pattern --"},{"time":443099,"text":"this is with the psychologists Yoel Inbar and Paul Bloom --"},{"time":446401,"text":"that in fact, across three studies we kept finding"},{"time":450421,"text":"that people who reported that they were easily disgusted"},{"time":452942,"text":"also reported that they were more politically conservative."},{"time":456397,"text":"Another way to say this, though, is that people"},{"time":458281,"text":"who are very liberal are very hard to disgust. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":463688,"text":"In a more recent follow-up study, we were able to look at"},{"time":467958,"text":"a much greater sample, a much larger sample. In this case,"},{"time":470639,"text":"this is nearly 30,000 U.S. respondents,"},{"time":473231,"text":"and we find the same pattern. As you can see,"},{"time":476008,"text":"people who are on the very conservative side"},{"time":477953,"text":"of answering the political orientation scale are"},{"time":480655,"text":"also much more likely to report that they're easily disgusted."},{"time":483425,"text":"This data set also allowed us to statistically control"},{"time":485920,"text":"for a number of things that we knew were both related"},{"time":488144,"text":"to political orientation and to disgust sensitivity."},{"time":491059,"text":"So we were able to control for gender, age, income,"},{"time":493664,"text":"education, even basic personality variables,"},{"time":496955,"text":"and the result stays the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":499257,"text":"When we actually looked at not just self-reported political orientation,"},{"time":502683,"text":"but voting behavior, we were able to look geographically"},{"time":505583,"text":"across the nation. What we found was that in regions"},{"time":508529,"text":"in which people reported high levels of disgust sensitivity,"},{"time":512426,"text":"McCain got more votes."},{"time":514413,"text":"So it not only predicted self-reported political orientation,"},{"time":517531,"text":"but actual voting behavior. And also we were able,"},{"time":519903,"text":"with this sample, to look across the world,"},{"time":522595,"text":"in 121 different countries we asked the same questions,"},{"time":526189,"text":"and as you can see, this is 121 countries collapsed"},{"time":530116,"text":"into 10 different geographical regions."},{"time":532486,"text":"No matter where you look, what this is plotting is the size"},{"time":535110,"text":"of the relationship between disgust sensitivity and political orientation,"},{"time":538521,"text":"and no matter where we looked, we saw a very similar effect."},{"time":542160,"text":"Other labs have actually looked at this as well"},{"time":545597,"text":"using different measures of disgust sensitivity,"},{"time":547774,"text":"so rather than asking people how easily disgusted they are,"},{"time":550326,"text":"they hook people up to physiological measures,"},{"time":552666,"text":"in this case skin conductance."},{"time":554294,"text":"And what they've demonstrated is that people who report"},{"time":556522,"text":"being more politically conservative are also more physiologically aroused"},{"time":560648,"text":"when you show them disgusting images like the ones that I showed you."},{"time":564222,"text":"Interestingly, what they also showed in a finding"},{"time":566391,"text":"that we kept getting in our previous studies as well"},{"time":570416,"text":"was that one of the strongest influences here is that"},{"time":574163,"text":"individuals who are very disgust-sensitive not only are"},{"time":576373,"text":"more likely to report being politically conservative, but"},{"time":578459,"text":"they're also very much more opposed to gay marriage"},{"time":581468,"text":"and homosexuality and pretty much a lot of"},{"time":583617,"text":"the socio-moral issues in the sexual domain."},{"time":587382,"text":"So physiological arousal predicted, in this study,"},{"time":590871,"text":"attitudes toward gay marriage."}]},{"cues":[{"time":592569,"text":"But even with all these data linking disgust sensitivity"},{"time":595788,"text":"and political orientation, one of the questions that remains is"},{"time":598947,"text":"what is the causal link here? Is it the case that"},{"time":602018,"text":"disgust really is shaping political and moral beliefs?"},{"time":605292,"text":"We have to resort to experimental methods to answer this,"},{"time":607852,"text":"and so what we can do is actually bring people into the lab"},{"time":610627,"text":"and disgust them and compare them to a control group"},{"time":613050,"text":"that hasn't been disgusted. It turns out that over"},{"time":615458,"text":"the past five years a number of researchers have done this,"},{"time":618186,"text":"and by and large the results have all been the same,"},{"time":621012,"text":"that when people are feeling disgust, their attitudes"},{"time":623441,"text":"shift towards the right of the political spectrum,"},{"time":625544,"text":"toward more moral conservatism as well."},{"time":628220,"text":"So this is whether you use a foul odor, a bad taste,"},{"time":631900,"text":"from film clips, from post-hypnotic suggestions of disgust,"},{"time":637190,"text":"images like the ones I've shown you, even just"},{"time":639556,"text":"reminding people that disease is prevalent and they should"},{"time":641519,"text":"be wary of it and wash up, right, to keep clean,"},{"time":645158,"text":"these all have similar effects on judgment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":647938,"text":"Let me just give you an example from a recent study"},{"time":650304,"text":"that we conducted. We asked participants"},{"time":653264,"text":"to just simply give us their opinion of a variety of social groups,"},{"time":657961,"text":"and we either made the room smell gross or not."},{"time":662373,"text":"When the room smelled gross, what we saw was that"},{"time":665544,"text":"individuals actually reported more negative attitudes toward gay men."},{"time":669215,"text":"Disgust didn't influence attitudes toward all the other"},{"time":671438,"text":"social groups that we asked, including African-Americans,"},{"time":673831,"text":"the elderly. It really came down to the attitudes they had"},{"time":677693,"text":"toward gay men."},{"time":679086,"text":"In another set of studies we actually simply reminded people --"},{"time":682647,"text":"this was at a time when the swine flu was going around --"},{"time":684573,"text":"we reminded people that in order to prevent the spread"},{"time":687057,"text":"of the flu that they ought to wash their hands."},{"time":690775,"text":"For some participants, we actually had them take questionnaires"},{"time":695190,"text":"next to a sign that reminded them to wash their hands."},{"time":698111,"text":"And what we found was that just taking a questionnaire"},{"time":700631,"text":"next to this hand-sanitizing reminder made individuals"},{"time":704344,"text":"report being more politically conservative."},{"time":707507,"text":"And when we asked them a variety of questions about"},{"time":709544,"text":"the rightness or wrongness of certain acts, what we also"},{"time":712967,"text":"found was that simply being reminded that they ought"},{"time":715282,"text":"to wash their hands made them more morally conservative."},{"time":718591,"text":"In particular, when we asked them questions about"},{"time":720888,"text":"sort of taboo but fairly harmless sexual practices,"},{"time":724662,"text":"just being reminded that they ought to wash their hands"},{"time":727288,"text":"made them think that they were more morally wrong."},{"time":729851,"text":"Let me give you an example of what I mean by harmless"},{"time":732251,"text":"but taboo sexual practice. We gave them scenarios."},{"time":735016,"text":"One of them said a man is house-sitting for his grandmother."},{"time":738774,"text":"When his grandmother's away, he has sex with his girlfriend"},{"time":741492,"text":"on his grandma's bed."},{"time":742840,"text":"In another one, we said a woman enjoys masturbating"},{"time":745337,"text":"with her favorite teddy bear cuddled next to her. (Laughter)"},{"time":749231,"text":"People find these to be more morally abhorrent"},{"time":751863,"text":"if they've been reminded to wash their hands. (Laughter)"},{"time":756179,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":759371,"text":"Okay. The fact that emotions influence our judgment"},{"time":762900,"text":"should come as no surprise. I mean,"},{"time":764783,"text":"that's part of how emotions work."},{"time":766184,"text":"They not only motivate you to behave in certain ways,"},{"time":767748,"text":"but they change the way you think."},{"time":769832,"text":"In the case of disgust, what is a little bit more surprising"},{"time":772622,"text":"is the scope of this influence. It makes perfect sense,"},{"time":776067,"text":"and it's a very good emotion for us to have, that disgust"},{"time":778946,"text":"would make me change the way that I perceive"},{"time":781602,"text":"the physical world whenever contamination is possible."},{"time":784645,"text":"It makes less sense that an emotion that was built"},{"time":787577,"text":"to prevent me from ingesting poison should predict"},{"time":790483,"text":"who I'm going to vote for in the upcoming presidential election."}]},{"cues":[{"time":793859,"text":"The question of whether disgust ought to influence"},{"time":796667,"text":"our moral and political judgments"},{"time":799019,"text":"certainly has to be complex, and might depend on exactly"},{"time":802155,"text":"what judgments we're talking about, and as a scientist,"},{"time":804837,"text":"we have to conclude sometimes that the scientific method"},{"time":806843,"text":"is just ill-equipped to answer these sorts of questions."},{"time":810347,"text":"But one thing that I am fairly certain about is,"},{"time":812395,"text":"at the very least, what we can do with this research is"},{"time":815214,"text":"point to what questions we ought to ask in the first place."},{"time":818066,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}